text:
The British grant program for Russian music organizations is ending

01 Nov 2019, 13:49

Until November 18, the Department of Culture and Education of the British Embassy in Moscow accepts applications from Russian organizations working in the music field for the third, final round of the grant program as part of the Year of Music of Great Britain and Russia 2019.
According to the site of the Year of Music, Russian organizations are invited to participate in the grant program, planning joint projects with British performers in Russia from December 1, 2019 to February 29, 2020.
Apply for a grant can:

public and private concert halls;
Philharmonic and conservatory;
theaters
clubs and bars;
independent agencies and promoters;
state and independent music festivals;
other cultural institutions with music programs and projects (museums, parks, etc.);
orchestras, ensembles, musical groups or performers with experience in organizing concerts and planning events with the participation of British performers.

The grant can be used for the following purposes:

musical performance of any genre: festival, concert, performance, opera, DJ set, audiovisual installation, etc., taking place in Russia with the participation of British musicians, soloists, conductors;
TV and radio broadcasts dedicated to music, live broadcast or recording of music programs, online projects;
conferences, seminars, lectures, exhibitions, advertising campaigns and other additional events, provided that they accompany live musical performances.

The application form is available for download on the website of the Year of Music of Great Britain and Russia 2019, applications are accepted at cultural.section.moscow@gmail.com. The results of the competition will be announced before the end of November 2019.
